sec.p:
We assume the insurance industry is competitive, with many identical insurance companies indexed by
j ∈ { 1 , 2 , … , J }
. The insurance companies compete by offering a menu of insurance policies to the employers.

There are many individuals indexed by
i ∈ { 1 , 2 , … , N }
. The individuals are identical except for their health type, as described by the exogenous probability of requiring medical care. The individuals inelastically supply their labor to one of the employers, and their labor wages are the only source of income, which the individuals may use to purchase a health insurance policy from the menu offered by their employer.
